## 🚀 Performance & DX
- Use `$derived` instead of chaining `$effect`.
- Cleanup intervals/subscriptions inside `$effect(() => () => cleanup())`.
- Favor small, composable components.
- Avoid unnecessary global stores.
- Keep DOM reactivity simple — `$state` → `$derived` → markup.
- Use `$derived.by()` for complex computations instead of `$effect`.

