## ❌ Anti-Patterns (Svelte 4 — DO NOT USE)

### Never use these Svelte 4 patterns:

**❌ `export let` for props:**
```svelte
<!-- WRONG -->
<script>
  export let name: string;
</script>
```
```svelte
<!-- CORRECT -->
<script lang="ts">
  interface Props {
    name: string;
  }
  let { name }: Props = $props();
</script>
```

**❌ `$:` reactive statements:**
```svelte
<!-- WRONG -->
<script>
  let count = 0;
  $: doubled = count * 2;
  $: {
    console.log(count);
  }
</script>
```
```svelte
<!-- CORRECT -->
<script lang="ts">
  const count = $state(0);
  const doubled = $derived(count * 2);
  $effect(() => console.log(count));
</script>
```

**❌ `on:click` event handlers:**
```svelte
<!-- WRONG -->
<button on:click={handler}>Click</button>
```
```svelte
<!-- CORRECT -->
<script lang="ts">
  function onclick() {
    // handler logic
  }
</script>
<button {onclick}>Click</button>
```

**❌ `createEventDispatcher`:**
```svelte
<!-- WRONG -->
<script>
  import { createEventDispatcher } from 'svelte';
  const dispatch = createEventDispatcher();
  dispatch('click', data);
</script>
```
```svelte
<!-- CORRECT -->
<script lang="ts">
  interface Props {
    onclick?: (data: any) => void;
  }
  let { onclick }: Props = $props();
  onclick?.(data);
</script>
```

**❌ `<slot>` for content:**
```svelte
<!-- WRONG -->
<div>
  <slot />
  <slot name="footer" />
</div>
```
```svelte
<!-- CORRECT -->
<script lang="ts">
  interface Props {
    children?: import('svelte').Snippet;
    footer?: import('svelte').Snippet;
  }
  let { children, footer }: Props = $props();
</script>
<div>
  {#if children}
    {@render children()}
  {/if}
  {#if footer}
    {@render footer()}
  {/if}
</div>
```

**❌ `$$props` and `$$restProps`:**
```svelte
<!-- WRONG -->
<button {...$$restProps} on:click>...</button>
```
```svelte
<!-- CORRECT -->
<script lang="ts">
  let { onclick, ...rest } = $props();
</script>
<button {...rest} {onclick}>...</button>
```

